This bank teller will store gp and xp for use at a later time.

Please follow these steps for banking exp. Failure to do so may result in loss of gp, exp, or items. Do this for your own good. 

When you decide to bank a character, make the level 1 character you intended to transfer exp to first. Do not reuse names. 

Pick a time shortly after a reboot for banking. Do not do it on a day when their has been frequent crashes, or right after a crash. The server could crash again, and you could be left with nothing. 

Before entering the bank, transfer all gp and items to a friend. This includes equipped items (armor, weapons, boots, amulet). If you have no friend (  ), or no one is available on online to help you, you can try using the chest located in the back. 

To make sure your using the chest without problem, place an item of little worth or importance to you in the chest and close it. If you see the message, "1 item was stored successfully", you know it working. 

Place every time you have in the chest that you want to transfer. Remember, anything you leave on your old character may never be accessible again. 

Chest have a maximum capacity of 50 items. 

Do not try to keep item in the chest for more then one reboot. The Database may be reset without warning, meaning you lose everything in it, without compensation.


After successfully transferring all items you want to keep, talk to the vault guard inside the cage in the bank. You can only deposit all your exp, not just a little. So, you will lose all your exp on your character. The amount of exp deposited it half of your total exp. 

Log off with your newly deleveled character, and log in with your level 1 character you made before. Quickly run into the bank, talk to the bank guard and withdraw your exp. Before you log out or beginning taking your level ups, its suggested you withdraw all items from the chest (if you used it), in case of possible complications. 

Once you have all your chest items, rest (to save your character), and go on your merry way. 



USE CHEST AT OWN RISK

If you followed every step stated above, and you still come across a problem, you can pm a DM on the forum.
